            <h4>What is the current population of Madison?</h4>
            <p>
                Based on the latest 2022 data from the US census, the
                current population of Madison is 2,838.  Madison, West Virginia is the 6,439th largest city in the US.
            </p>

            

            

            <h4>What was the peak population of Madison?</h4>
            <p>
                
                    The peak population of Madison was in
                    1990, when its population was
                    3,246.
                    
                        In 1990, Madison was the
                        5,295th largest city in the US; now
                        its fallen to the 6,439th largest city in
                        the US.
                    
                    Madison is currently
                        <span style="color: red;">
                            12.6%
                            smaller
                        </span>
                        than it was in 1990.
                    </p>
                
            </p>
            
                
                    <h4>How quickly is Madison growing?</h4>
                
                <p>
                    
                        Madison has grown
                        4.5% 
                        since the 2000.
                    


                    
                        Madison, West Virginia is growing somewhat quickly;
                        it is growing faster than 63%
                        of similarly sized cities since 2000.
                    
                </p>
            

            

            

            

    
    
        
    

    

    
   
    
